# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: StoryBeginnings | Scene: CoronationDay
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "A week later, the day of the coronation had arrived. All the preparations had been completed."
    new "A week later, the day of the coronation had arrived. All the preparations had been completed."

    old "Sarah had wanted to help out with the work for the coronation, but she hadn't found any time. Officially, she was sick for the week."
    new "Sarah had wanted to help out with the work for the coronation, but she hadn't found any time. Officially, she was sick for the week."

    old "In reality, Kate had kept her confined to the bedroom for most of the week."
    new "In reality, Kate had kept her confined to the bedroom for most of the week."

    old "Any time Sarah thought she might be able to get some work done, Kate would drag or lure her back into bed."
    new "Any time Sarah thought she might be able to get some work done, Kate would drag or lure her back into bed."

    old "Shamefully, Sarah had to admit to herself that she hadn't been able to resist Kate in the slighest."
    new "Shamefully, Sarah had to admit to herself that she hadn't been able to resist Kate in the slighest."

    old "Sarah had worked dilligently all week to prepare for this day."
    new "Sarah had worked dilligently all week to prepare for this day."

    old "No expense had been spared, as per the instructions from the council."
    new "No expense had been spared, as per the instructions from the council."

    old "Noble families from across the realm had gathered, filling up the entire great hall."
    new "Noble families from across the realm had gathered, filling up the entire great hall."

    old "Matching the endless decorations, were the tables, filled to the brim with food prepared by the royal chef."
    new "Matching the endless decorations, were the tables, filled to the brim with food prepared by the royal chef."

    old "Everyone in attendance seemed entranced by the display."
    new "Everyone in attendance seemed entranced by the display."

    old "Thomas, for his part, sat uncomfortably on the throne."
    new "Thomas, for his part, sat uncomfortably on the throne."

    old "As per the instructions, the castle was sparsely decorated."
    new "As per the instructions, the castle was sparsely decorated."

    old "Only the most important noble families had been called into attendance."
    new "Only the most important noble families had been called into attendance."

    old "With so few people present, the great hall somehow felt emptier than usual."
    new "With so few people present, the great hall somehow felt emptier than usual."

    old "Those invited seemed confused, looking around for decorations that weren't there."
    new "Those invited seemed confused, looking around for decorations that weren't there."

    old "Thomas, for his part, sat comfortably on the throne."
    new "Thomas, for his part, sat comfortably on the throne."

    old "Sarah had taken her place on the official dais, seated near Thomas, though on a slightly lower level."
    new "Sarah had taken her place on the official dais, seated near Thomas, though on a slightly lower level."

    old "From her seat, she could look out over the crowd."
    new "From her seat, she could look out over the crowd."

    old "Amongst the sea of faces, some jumped out."
    new "Amongst the sea of faces, some jumped out."

    old "Marion sat on the front row. Given his family name, nothing less could be expected."
    new "Marion sat on the front row. Given his family name, nothing less could be expected."

    old "Marion sat perfectly still, not engaging in the conversation around him. Had she not known him, Sarah might have confused him for a statue."
    new "Marion sat perfectly still, not engaging in the conversation around him. Had she not known him, Sarah might have confused him for a statue."

    old "Further in the back she noticed Varga, the young field commander she had met on the battlements."
    new "Further in the back she noticed Varga, the young field commander she had met on the battlements."

    old "By contrast, Varga seemed entirely distracted, busily trying to keep three young children from fidgeting in their seats."
    new "By contrast, Varga seemed entirely distracted, busily trying to keep three young children from fidgeting in their seats."

    old "Sarah wondered if they could be his children, but she saw no possible wife seated next to him. She knew so little about this man, who was important enough to have been invited today."
    new "Sarah wondered if they could be his children, but she saw no possible wife seated next to him. She knew so little about this man, who was important enough to have been invited today."

    old "Standing in the back of the room was Lady Carolyn, orchestrating a swarm of servants, calmly handing out instructions and orders."
    new "Standing in the back of the room was Lady Carolyn, orchestrating a swarm of servants, calmly handing out instructions and orders."

    old "After a few moments, a bell rung out over the hall, commanding everyone to silence."
    new "After a few moments, a bell rung out over the hall, commanding everyone to silence."

    old "The priests began to slowly walk across the carpet that had been rolled out through the center of the room."
    new "The priests began to slowly walk across the carpet that had been rolled out through the center of the room."

    old "At the front of the procession, was the high priest, carrying a velvet pillow with golden fringes."
    new "At the front of the procession, was the high priest, carrying a velvet pillow with golden fringes."

    old "Sitting atop the pillow was the crown."
    new "Sitting atop the pillow was the crown."

    old "Father's crown, Sarah thought, soon to be Thomas'."
    new "Father's crown, Sarah thought, soon to be Thomas'."

    old "The high priest slowly ascended the stairs until he stood next to Thomas."
    new "The high priest slowly ascended the stairs until he stood next to Thomas."

    old "High Priest\" \"Prince Thomas Rose, eldest of the Rose family, son of Orwell and heir to the throne, rise."
    new "High Priest\" \"Prince Thomas Rose, eldest of the Rose family, son of Orwell and heir to the throne, rise."

    old "Thomas stood up, as instructed."
    new "Thomas stood up, as instructed."

    old "High Priest\" \"Do you swear to uphold the virtues of your elders, and commit your life to the protection of the nation of Rosanna."
    new "High Priest\" \"Do you swear to uphold the virtues of your elders, and commit your life to the protection of the nation of Rosanna."

    old "I do."
    new "I do."

    old "High Priest\" \"Should you speak falsely, what would you desire of the gods?"
    new "High Priest\" \"Should you speak falsely, what would you desire of the gods?"

    old "Should I speak falsely, I pray that the gods strike me down as I stand."
    new "Should I speak falsely, I pray that the gods strike me down as I stand."

    old "For a moment, there was a pause, and the room was perfectly still."
    new "For a moment, there was a pause, and the room was perfectly still."

    old "This was the surrender, the moment where the king invited the gods to kill him, should his heart be untrue."
    new "This was the surrender, the moment where the king invited the gods to kill him, should his heart be untrue."

    old "If nothing happened, all present would take it as a sign of divine favor."
    new "If nothing happened, all present would take it as a sign of divine favor."

    old "The high priest nodded, seemingly content that no divine wrath had struck Thomas down."
    new "The high priest nodded, seemingly content that no divine wrath had struck Thomas down."

    old "High Priest\" \"Then by the grace of all gods, and in the presence of all the noble families, I declare you King Thomas Rose, sovereign of Rosanna."
    new "High Priest\" \"Then by the grace of all gods, and in the presence of all the noble families, I declare you King Thomas Rose, sovereign of Rosanna."

    old "The high priest placed the crown atop Thomas' head, and the room errupted into cheers and celebrations."
    new "The high priest placed the crown atop Thomas' head, and the room errupted into cheers and celebrations."

    old "Sarah herself breathed a sigh of relief. She knew the odds of something going wrong were low, but she hadn't been able to stop worrying until now."
    new "Sarah herself breathed a sigh of relief. She knew the odds of something going wrong were low, but she hadn't been able to stop worrying until now."

    old "Sarah stood up and joined in the applause for the newly crowned king."
    new "Sarah stood up and joined in the applause for the newly crowned king."

    old "Thomas waved to the people, the heavy crown sitting akwardly atop his head."
    new "Thomas waved to the people, the heavy crown sitting akwardly atop his head."

    old "There will be time, Sarah thought, for him to grow into it."
    new "There will be time, Sarah thought, for him to grow into it."

    old "Thomas turned for a short moment, looking at his sister. She saw him give her a small nod, acknowledging her."
    new "Thomas turned for a short moment, looking at his sister. She saw him give her a small nod, acknowledging her."

    old "After the official coronation had finished, the festivities could begin."
    new "After the official coronation had finished, the festivities could begin."

    old "Sarah watched as Thomas was all but dragged into the crowd, hands reaching out for him, hoping to catch a moment to congratulate the new king, and win some favor."
    new "Sarah watched as Thomas was all but dragged into the crowd, hands reaching out for him, hoping to catch a moment to congratulate the new king, and win some favor."

    old "Sarah remained behind. Where Thomas was going now, she couldn't help him."
    new "Sarah remained behind. Where Thomas was going now, she couldn't help him."

    old "Sarah scanned the room."
    new "Sarah scanned the room."

    old "On one end, she saw Marion, standing just beyond the mob. Apparently, he considered his family's reputation to be above begging for the new king's attention."
    new "On one end, she saw Marion, standing just beyond the mob. Apparently, he considered his family's reputation to be above begging for the new king's attention."

    old "On the other end, she saw Varga, kneeled down, speaking to the three children, too busy or unaware that he should be joining the horde of nobility swarming Thomas."
    new "On the other end, she saw Varga, kneeled down, speaking to the three children, too busy or unaware that he should be joining the horde of nobility swarming Thomas."

    old "Choose."
    new "Choose."

    old "Approach Marion."
    new "Approach Marion."

    old "Sarah walked over to Marion, standing apart from the crowd."
    new "Sarah walked over to Marion, standing apart from the crowd."

    old "Lord Marion."
    new "Lord Marion."

    old "Marion had spotted her coming towards him, and met her curtsy with a well timed bow."
    new "Marion had spotted her coming towards him, and met her curtsy with a well timed bow."

    old "Sarah couldn't help but be impressed with how effortless Marion could make everything look."
    new "Sarah couldn't help but be impressed with how effortless Marion could make everything look."

    old "Princess Sarah, my pleasure. Congratulations on your brother and our new sovereign."
    new "Princess Sarah, my pleasure. Congratulations on your brother and our new sovereign."

    old "Long may he reign."
    new "Long may he reign."

    old "Marion nodded."
    new "Marion nodded."

    old "Absolutely."
    new "Absolutely."

    old "There was a moment of silence."
    new "There was a moment of silence."

    old "Shouldn't you be off in the crowd with the other nobles, trying to win some points with our new sovereign?"
    new "Shouldn't you be off in the crowd with the other nobles, trying to win some points with our new sovereign?"

    old "Marion scoffed."
    new "Marion scoffed."

    old "I think the reputation of the Achillea family speaks for itself."
    new "I think the reputation of the Achillea family speaks for itself."

    old "Marion turned to Sarah."
    new "Marion turned to Sarah."

    old "Would you not agree?"
    new "Would you not agree?"

    old "I was only joking Marion, we know what you and your family means to this country."
    new "I was only joking Marion, we know what you and your family means to this country."

    old "Another silence."
    new "Another silence."

    old "You know, Marion, you could afford to relax every once in a while. You don't always need to be...like this."
    new "You know, Marion, you could afford to relax every once in a while. You don't always need to be...like this."

    old "Marion considered Sarah's words, staring at the floor."
    new "Marion considered Sarah's words, staring at the floor."

    old "I really can't..."
    new "I really can't..."

    old "Sarah looked at him with surprise."
    new "Sarah looked at him with surprise."

    old "What do you mean?"
    new "What do you mean?"

    old "Marion looked at her."
    new "Marion looked at her."

    old "I am the head of my family. We can trace our ancestry back for centuries, to the very founding of this nation."
    new "I am the head of my family. We can trace our ancestry back for centuries, to the very founding of this nation."

    old "At every step, each head of the Achillea family did their part. Each carried out their role and their task, to their best ability."
    new "At every step, each head of the Achillea family did their part. Each carried out their role and their task, to their best ability."

    old "This is how my family came to be as it is today."
    new "This is how my family came to be as it is today."

    old "We thrive, only because each generation managed to build on what the one before achieved. Like a large chain, each link, holding the other."
    new "We thrive, only because each generation managed to build on what the one before achieved. Like a large chain, each link, holding the other."

    old "Marion paused for a moment."
    new "Marion paused for a moment."

    old "Now it is my turn, the latest link in a chain that will continue to span for centuries after me. Unless..."
    new "Now it is my turn, the latest link in a chain that will continue to span for centuries after me. Unless..."

    old "Marion cleared his throat."
    new "Marion cleared his throat."

    old "Unless I prove weak. Because that is all it takes. One weak link, and the chain breaks."
    new "Unless I prove weak. Because that is all it takes. One weak link, and the chain breaks."

    old "Sarah listened intently to Marion. It wasn't often that he shared insights into his inner world."
    new "Sarah listened intently to Marion. It wasn't often that he shared insights into his inner world."

    old "You carry a lot on your shoulders, Marion."
    new "You carry a lot on your shoulders, Marion."

    old "Sarah placed her hands on his shoulders."
    new "Sarah placed her hands on his shoulders."

    old "But no man can bear such a burden forever. You should find opportunities or people to help you ease that burden."
    new "But no man can bear such a burden forever. You should find opportunities or people to help you ease that burden."

    old "Marion looked dejected."
    new "Marion looked dejected."

    old "You and your brother have each other. It's different for me."
    new "You and your brother have each other. It's different for me."

    old "Sarah continued to comfort him."
    new "Sarah continued to comfort him."

    old "It doesn't have to be family. There are a lot of people in this world that could help you. You just need to be open to them."
    new "It doesn't have to be family. There are a lot of people in this world that could help you. You just need to be open to them."

    old "Sarah and Marion continued to speak for some time."
    new "Sarah and Marion continued to speak for some time."

    old "Lost in conversation, Sarah suddenly noticed the coronation had all but ended."
    new "Lost in conversation, Sarah suddenly noticed the coronation had all but ended."

    old "Marion, it's getting late, I need to leave. But try to remember what I said, don't go around carrying the world on your back."
    new "Marion, it's getting late, I need to leave. But try to remember what I said, don't go around carrying the world on your back."

    old "Marion bowed."
    new "Marion bowed."

    old "I will take what you said into consideration, Sarah, thank you for speaking to me. It really does mean a lot to me."
    new "I will take what you said into consideration, Sarah, thank you for speaking to me. It really does mean a lot to me."

    old "Sarah waved to Marion as she went to exit the great hall."
    new "Sarah waved to Marion as she went to exit the great hall."

    old "Poor Marion, she thought to herself. He projects composure, at all times, but it isolates him from everyone around him."
    new "Poor Marion, she thought to herself. He projects composure, at all times, but it isolates him from everyone around him."

    old "Sarah wondered how lonely her life without Thomas would be. She dared not to dwell on that thought for long."
    new "Sarah wondered how lonely her life without Thomas would be. She dared not to dwell on that thought for long."

    old "Sarah left the great hall and wandered back to her bedroom. She needed to sleep."
    new "Sarah left the great hall and wandered back to her bedroom. She needed to sleep."

    old "Approach Varga."
    new "Approach Varga."

    old "Sarah walked over to Varga, standing apart from the crowd."
    new "Sarah walked over to Varga, standing apart from the crowd."

    old "She came up behind him."
    new "She came up behind him."

    old "Lord Varga."
    new "Lord Varga."

    old "Varga jumped up and turned around, caught unaware by her approach. He quickly fumbled into a bow."
    new "Varga jumped up and turned around, caught unaware by her approach. He quickly fumbled into a bow."

    old "Princess Sarah! Good to see you again."
    new "Princess Sarah! Good to see you again."

    old "Varga turned to the children."
    new "Varga turned to the children."

    old "Come on, bow, this is the princess."
    new "Come on, bow, this is the princess."

    old "Varga waved his hands at them, instructing them to follow his example. Each produced a similarly clumsy bow."
    new "Varga waved his hands at them, instructing them to follow his example. Each produced a similarly clumsy bow."

    old "Sarah humored the children by bowing in return."
    new "Sarah humored the children by bowing in return."

    old "These are your...?"
    new "These are your...?"

    old "My two sisters and my little brother."
    new "My two sisters and my little brother."

    old "Varga clarified."
    new "Varga clarified."

    old "Sarah seemed surprised, they seemed a ways younger than Varga."
    new "Sarah seemed surprised, they seemed a ways younger than Varga."

    old "Varga noticed Sarah's confusion and continued."
    new "Varga noticed Sarah's confusion and continued."

    old "My mother died when I was born, and my father remarried several years later with their mother, that's why there is such an age difference."
    new "My mother died when I was born, and my father remarried several years later with their mother, that's why there is such an age difference."

    old "His half brothers and half sister."
    new "His half brothers and half sister."

    old "During the insurrection, my father was one of the men who tried to maintain the peace. For this efforts, they gave him the rope."
    new "During the insurrection, my father was one of the men who tried to maintain the peace. For this efforts, they gave him the rope."

    old "I managed to escape the mob and saved my brothers and sister. I've been taking care of them ever since."
    new "I managed to escape the mob and saved my brothers and sister. I've been taking care of them ever since."

    old "Sarah was surprised by how casually Varga shared his trauma, and how little it seemed to faze him."
    new "Sarah was surprised by how casually Varga shared his trauma, and how little it seemed to faze him."

    old "Even a fraction of such suffering seemed unimaginable to Sarah, but for Varga, and the world he grew up in, it was common."
    new "Even a fraction of such suffering seemed unimaginable to Sarah, but for Varga, and the world he grew up in, it was common."

    old "I'm so sorry for your loss."
    new "I'm so sorry for your loss."

    old "Varga bowed his head."
    new "Varga bowed his head."

    old "Thank you princess, your concern means a lot to me. To all of us."
    new "Thank you princess, your concern means a lot to me. To all of us."

    old "Varga straightened his back."
    new "Varga straightened his back."

    old "But let's not talk about these depressing things. Today is a celebration, after all. Congratulations on your brother."
    new "But let's not talk about these depressing things. Today is a celebration, after all. Congratulations on your brother."

    old "I'm sure he will make a great king."
    new "I'm sure he will make a great king."

    old "Sarah looked at Varga."
    new "Sarah looked at Varga."

    old "What makes you say that?"
    new "What makes you say that?"

    old "Varga paused for a moment, considering his answer."
    new "Varga paused for a moment, considering his answer."

    old "He strikes me as someone with a kind heart. Too many rulers think that a strong leader means having a cold heart."
    new "He strikes me as someone with a kind heart. Too many rulers think that a strong leader means having a cold heart."

    old "I think it's the opposite. Without kindness, you forget what you do it all for...for the people you rule."
    new "I think it's the opposite. Without kindness, you forget what you do it all for...for the people you rule."

    old "King Thomas, I suspect, will care for both the nobles and the common folk. Or, at least, I hope so."
    new "King Thomas, I suspect, will care for both the nobles and the common folk. Or, at least, I hope so."

    old "Sarah nodded along."
    new "Sarah nodded along."

    old "I think you're right, lord Varga. My brother has a kind heart. But ruling will be new to him, there is a lot for him to learn."
    new "I think you're right, lord Varga. My brother has a kind heart. But ruling will be new to him, there is a lot for him to learn."

    old "Varga agreed."
    new "Varga agreed."

    old "Certainly, princess. If I can ever be of any help, you need only ask me."
    new "Certainly, princess. If I can ever be of any help, you need only ask me."

    old "Varga made an offer as so many others had, but unlike them, he seemed to have a genuine desire to help."
    new "Varga made an offer as so many others had, but unlike them, he seemed to have a genuine desire to help."

    old "Thank you for that offer. King Thomas and myself will certainly call on you, should we need your aid."
    new "Thank you for that offer. King Thomas and myself will certainly call on you, should we need your aid."

    old "The children began to run circles around Sarah, grabbing and pulling on her dress."
    new "The children began to run circles around Sarah, grabbing and pulling on her dress."

    old "Hey! Stop that! Leave the princess alone!"
    new "Hey! Stop that! Leave the princess alone!"

    old "Sarah could only laugh."
    new "Sarah could only laugh."

    old "It's ok, let them, they're not doing any harm."
    new "It's ok, let them, they're not doing any harm."

    old "Sarah continued speaking with Varga and playing with the children for some time."
    new "Sarah continued speaking with Varga and playing with the children for some time."

    old "Before she knew it, the coronation had mostly drawn to an end."
    new "Before she knew it, the coronation had mostly drawn to an end."

    old "Varga and his family, they had made her completely forget to play politics."
    new "Varga and his family, they had made her completely forget to play politics."

    old "She was grateful for the distraction."
    new "She was grateful for the distraction."

    old "With the hour drawing late, Sarah thanked Varga for his time and waved goodbye to the children."
    new "With the hour drawing late, Sarah thanked Varga for his time and waved goodbye to the children."

    old "She returned to her bedroom, desperately in need of sleep."
    new "She returned to her bedroom, desperately in need of sleep."

